'''Rajalakshmi Engineering College''' ('''R.E.C''') ({{lang-ta|<U+0BB0><U+0BBE><U+0B9C><U+0BB2><U+0B9F><U+0BCD><U+0B9A><U+0BC1><U+0BAE><U+0BBF> <U+0BAA><U+0BCA><U+0BB1><U+0BBF><U+0BAF><U+0BBF><U+0BAF><U+0BB2><U+0BCD> <U+0B95><U+0BB2><U+0BCD><U+0BB2><U+0BC2><U+0BB0><U+0BBF>}}), ({{lang-hi|<U+0930><U+093E><U+091C><U+0932><U+0915><U+094D><U+0937><U+094D><U+092E><U+0940> <U+0907><U+0902><U+091C><U+0940><U+0928><U+093F><U+092F><U+0930><U+093F><U+0902><U+0917> <U+0915><U+0949><U+0932><U+0947><U+091C>}}), is a recognized <ref>[http://rmkec.ac.in/engg.pdf], [[The Hindu]], November 2012</ref> [[Private university|private]] [[Engineering|technical]] [[co-educational]] engineering/management college, located at [[Thandalam, Chennai|Thandalam]], [[Sriperumbudur]] near [[Chennai]], Tamil Nadu, India. The college was established in 1997 by the Rajalakshmi Educational Trust, [[Rajalakshmi Institutions]]<ref>http://www.rajalakshmiinstitutes.edu.in Rajalakshmi Institutions</ref> and has been approved by [[All India Council of Technical Education]] (AICTE), New Delhi. It is an affiliate of [[Anna University]], South India. The college has been awarded ISO9001: 2000 certificate for academic standard by TUV Suddeutschland, Germany. [[University Grants Commission (India)|University Grants Commission]] confirmed the conferment of Autonomous status to Rajalakshmi Engineering College for a period of 5 years with effect from 2010-11 to 2015-16.<ref>http://www.ugc.ac.in/oldpdf/commissiondecision/468.pdf</ref><ref>http://www.ugc.ac.in/oldpdf/colleges/374autocolleges_april11.pdf</ref><ref>http://www.ugc.ac.in/oldpdf/colleges/autonomous_colleges-list.pdf</ref> The college is located near [[Hyundai Motors]] and [[SIPCOT]].

==History==

===Initial years===

In 1997, the college was granted permission to conduct engineering courses in the disciplines of [[Mechanical Engineering]], [[Electronics and Communication Engineering]] and [[Computer Science Engineering]], awarded by the [[Anna University]].

The college city office at New Avadi Road, [[Kilpauk]] (near [[Purasawalkam]]) [[Chennai]] was inaugurated on 1997.

[[File:Rajalakshmi Institutions Main Head Office.jpg|350px|thumb|right|Rajalakshmi Engineering College Main Office]]

===Expansion===

The college was later expanded with 11 undergraduate and 11 postgraduate programs.The college started the [[Electrical and Electronics Engineering]] and Information Technology in 1999 and followed by [[Automobile Engineering]] in the year 2006, Automobile Department of Rajalakshmi Engineering College ranks good after [[Madras Institute of Technology]] under Anna University affiliation. [[Aeronautical Engineering]] in the year 2005, [[Biomedical Engineering]], [[Biotechnology]] and [[Civil Engineering]].The college also started to offer BEd and MEd programmes in 2006, Nursing in the year 2008.One of the integral course under civil and construction department named BArch (Architecture) was also started in the year 2011 and approved by [[Council of Architecture]].The Premier Engineering college to start the course of Architecture.

