==Accreditations==

The college is an ISO 9001:2008 certified institution. REC was awarded the [[ISO 9002|International Organization for Standardization 9002]] certificate by [[T<U+00DC>V NORD]] of [[Hanover]] and [[T<U+00DC>V S<U+00DC>D]] of [[Munich]], Germany. It is approved and accredited by the [[National Board of Accreditation]] (NBA)<ref name="rajalakshmi1">http://www.rajalakshmi.org/profile-accreditations.html</ref> of [[AICTE]]. The [[National Assessment and Accreditation Council]] (NAAC)<ref name="rajalakshmi1"/> has accredited the college for a period of five years with validity from 31 March 2007.

The college is accredited by companies like [[Tata Consultancy Services]], [[Cognizant Technology Solutions]], WIPRO Trusted Academic Partner and [[Infosys]] [http://campusconnect.infosys.com/Registration/StudentRegistration.aspx Campus Connect].<ref name="rajalakshmi1"/>
[[Ashok Leyland]] recognized the college as a centre of excellence in automotives. [[IBM]] named it a "Centre of Excellence for Certified Software Center".<ref name="rajalakshmi1"/>

Programmes at REC are accredited by the [[Institution of Engineers (India)|Institution of Engineers]], India (IEI).

