== Rajalakshmi Education Private Limited ==
The Rajalakshmi Education Private Limited<ref>http://www.scoop.it/t/international-education-in-australia/p/1441311130/educational-institutions-sign-mou-ibnlive-com</ref> has also signed MoUs with [[University of Worcester]], UK,<ref name="rajalakshmi2"/><ref>http://indalytics.com/2012/03/rajalakshmi-education-to-work-with-university-of-worcester/</ref> to jointly offer courses in Computing and Management.<ref>http://www.rajalakshmieducation.in/mou-repl-uow.pdf</ref><ref>http://yourdailyupdateblog.com/archives/28448</ref> The college is recognised as a scientific and Industrial Organization by the [[Department of Scientific and Industrial Research (India)|Department of Scientific and Industrial Research]] (DSIR)<ref name="rajalakshmi2"/> Government of India.They are actively engaged in R&D activities aiming at the development of innovative processes and products. Based on the strength of such R&D activities.The Rajalakshmi Engineering College also signed [[Memorandum of Understanding]] (MoUs) with [[Edexcel]],<ref name="ReferenceA">http://www.rajalakshmieducation.in/about-repl.html</ref> a UK company, is one of England, [[Wales]] and [[Northern Ireland]]'s five main [[examination board]]s, and is wholly owned by Pearson, the world's largest education publishing and technology company which is part of Pearson PLC, the global publisher and owner of Penguin and Financial Times. Its name is a [[portmanteau]] word derived from the words "educational" and "excellence". The company offers a variety of qualifications, including [[Advanced level (UK)|A level]]s (GCEs), [[GCSE]]s and the [[Business And Technology Education Council (BTEC)|BTEC]] suite of vocational qualifications. It also offers work-based learning qualifications <U+2013> including BTEC Apprenticeships and NVQs <U+2013> via Pearson Work Based Learning.
REPL has been recognised as an International center by Edexcel for the following certification programmes.
*Edexcel BTEC Level 5 HND Higher National Diploma of Edexcel, UK<ref name="ReferenceA"/>
*Edexcel BTEC Level 7 Extended Diploma in Strategic Management.<ref name="ReferenceA"/>

REPL currently offers the following programmes which are in great demand in India and abroad<ref name="rajalakshmieducation.in">http://rajalakshmieducation.in</ref>
*Master of Science (MSc) Business or Master of Business Administration (MBA) Strategic Management
*Bachelor of Science (BSc <U+2013> Hons) Computing
*Bachelor of Science (BSc <U+2013> Hons) Computer Games Design and Development

==Interaction & Partnership with Aircel Chennai Open==
Rajalakshmi Engineering College (Rajalakshmi Institutions) has also been the official partner of the [[Aircel Chennai Open]] from [[2012 Aircel Chennai Open]]<ref>http://www.aircelchennaiopen.org/2012/sponsors</ref><ref>[http://www.rajalakshmiinstitutes.edu.in Rajalakshmi Institutions]</ref> and [[2013 Aircel Chennai Open]].<ref>http://www.aircelchennaiopen.org/2013/sponsors</ref> The Chennai Open (also known during its run as the ''Gold Flake Open'' and the ''Tata Open'') is a professional tennis tournament played on [[Hard (tennis)|outdoor hard courts]]. It is currently part of the [[ATP World Tour 250 series]] of the [[Association of Tennis Professionals|Association of Tennis Professionals (ATP) World Tour]]. It is held annually in January at the [[SDAT Tennis Stadium]] in Chennai, [[Tamil Nadu]], India.

==Conferences, Symposiums & Workshops==
Rajalakshmi Engineering College in association with the International Union of Surface Finishers and the Singapore Surface Engineering Association is organising an International conference on Surface Engineering for Research and Industrial Applications called '''Interfinish SERIA 2013 Asia Pacific''' from 7 August to 9,2013.<ref>https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/aero-chennai/T8SWJbGVJAk</ref> The event inaugurated by Padma Bushan Dr V K Saraswat, Former Secretary, Department of Defence R&D and DG DRDO and SA to RM.<ref>http://www.seria2013.rajalakshmi.org/about.html</ref><ref>http://www.academia.edu/3397960/InterFinish-SERIA_2013_at_Rajalakshmi_Group_of_Institutions_Chennai_India</ref><ref>http://www.livechennai.com/detailnews.asp?newsid=6351</ref>
The conference has over 9 plenary speakers, 70 keynote speakers and invited speakers along with over 100 paper presentations from researchers from both academics and industry. Participants from countries such as USA, UK, Russia, Korea, Malaysia, Singapore, Spain and Malta have confirmed their registrations. Parallel Workshops on Heat Treatment, corrosion protection, plasma coatings, cyanide free plating and nanotechnology by experts from UK, Korea, Singapore and India is planned for academicians, students and practising engineers.<ref>http://newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/International-conference-on-surface-engineering-from-August-7/2013/07/31/article1709870.ece</ref><ref>http://www.seria2013.rajalakshmi.org/</ref>
Addressing the launch of the event, Vijay Kumar Saraswat, former Secretary, Department of Defence R&D, Director-General DRDO and Scientific Advisor to Defence Minister,<ref>http://www.deccanchronicle.com/130808/news-current-affairs/article/microbes-revolutionise-desalination-technology</ref> said surface engineering techniques find application in areas ranging from automotive, aerospace, missile, power, electronic to biomedical.<ref>http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/states/surface-engineering-can-prevent-wear-corrosion-loss-vk-saraswat/article4999914.ece</ref>

